  "name": "Cataracts - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Procedures)",
  "description": "Simulates an ophthalmologist identifying their complete cataract patient population. Combines: cataract diagnosis codes (multi-type) and cataract surgery procedures. Tests Condition + Procedure cross-resource union for lens disorder.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete cataract patient population for a quality improvement initiative on surgical timing and post-op outcomes. From clinical experience, cataract patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal cataract diagnosis (parent cataract, bilateral, unilateral, or nuclear cataract), and many have undergone cataract surgery.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any cataract diagnosis\n2. Patients who have undergone cataract surgery\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
